JOHANNESBURG - Forty-seven more people have died in South Africa after contracting the coronavirus, pushing the death toll to 52,710. The Health Department said that 548 infections were also picked up over the past 24 hours, bring the known caseload to 1,546,000. 1,472,000 people have so far recuperated, with the country's recovery rate holding steady at 95%. On the vaccine front, over 239,000 healthcare workers have got the jab. 29 March 2021 #COVID19 statistics in South Africa #CoronaVirusSA pic.twitter.com/Ua9qf0Mp1Q  As of today the cumulative number of #COVID19 cases for South Africa is 1 545 979. oday, 47 COVID-19 related deaths have been reported which brings the total to 52 710 deaths Our cumulative recoveries today stand at 1 472 645, representing a recovery rate of 95%. pic.twitter.com/UD4wWemTcG  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.